details.locationDescription: The Dublin Pub has been ranked one of the Top 10 Pubs in the US. This authentic Irish Pub prides itself in their Irish/American/European menu and the honor of being the #1 Jameson account in Ohio as well as the largest St. Patrick's Day in Ohio. While being one of the top Guinness destinations in the Midwest, they also pride themselves as being a top seller of local microbreweries. Established in 1998, this historic pub gained new legendary status in 2014 when it added an addition salvaging and rebuilding a 100 year old church adding two new rooms for private parties that seat up to 150 people combined. Sheryl Crow, The Violent Femmes, Blue Oyster Cult, Berlin, Gaelic Storm and a host of other Irish and Celtic bands have played there since 1998.

snippet.text: Big thanks for helping make our trip to Dublin amazing.
details.locationDescription: The Ha’penny Bridge Inn has been in continuous use as a Public House since the middle of the 19th Century. The building originally dates from 1732, but has existed, relatively unchanged since 1825 when the current incarnation of Wellington Quay was completed. The Ha’penny Bridge, built in 1816 was originally called the Iron Bridge, but the name slowly evolved as it was a toll bridge which charged the princely sum of one halfpenny to cross the Liffey. The pub offers some of the best views in the city of this historical landmark in the centre of Dublin In the early 20th Century the pub became “Murray’s” and was eventually taken over by Josef Locke the renowned Irish Tenor and subject of the film “Hear my Song” who not only owned the pub, but resided in the apartment upstairs for most of the 1960’s. It was also a popular spot visited frequently by Phil Lynnott and his bandmates from Thin Lizzy in their formative years. The pub was then purchased by Michael Ryan in 1987 from Tipperary.

details.locationDescription: La Maison is a French Brasserie in the Heart of Dublin, specialising in some wonderful French classics along with some innovative and modern cooking using the best of locally sourced fresh Irish produce. La Maison has been a City Centre favourite for over 20 years. Situated at 15 Castle Market, in Dublin’s famous Creative Quarter an area associated with design and creativity since the 18th century. This beautiful red sandstone brick building has been here for 150 years and has had many different functions over the years leading to a wonderful cosy and quirky interior. Beautiful artwork by Leonetto Cappiello, L’oir Dor, and Diable Vent, all sourced from Paris at Puces market adorn the walls. Doisneau photographs line the stairs offering a touch of romance to this relaxed space. On the second level the dining room is light and airy, with sash windows looking out onto the bustling Castle Market Street.

snippet.text: Its not a spot for a cheap meal but if you want the best steak in Dublin
details.locationDescription: Dublin's original steakhouse with the experience and knowledge of over 25 years of serving the perfect steak. We change our menus each season to reflect the best that Irish produce has to offer and to ensure the highest quality of local fresh seafood. We offer an informed wine list to meet all budgets and an extensive selection of cocktails and spirits. We are also open for weekday for lunch serving health and tasty dishes at very reasonable prices. The way in which we guarantee the highest quality in beef in both texture and flavour is by choosing Irish beef and the highest grade of traditional breeds of cattle. At F.X.BUCKLEY our prime cuts are hung on the bone at 4°C and at 80% humidity for a minimum of 28 days. Storing meat for several weeks where it can loose up to 16% of it's weight involves considerable expertise so all F.X.BUCKLEY butchers are specifically trained for the process. The benefit for our patrons is to experience the concentration and saturation of natural meat flavours and superior tenderness. Hence why you will hear experts use terms such as "buttery and rich", and "earthy and nutty" to describe our dry-aged beef.

The Chawke Pub Group has restored this historic Dublin pub to its former greatness. Established in 1845 Searson's has earned it's place in history, step inside and you will experience a beautifully restored bar, excellent service, the finest food and drink, and that friendly, warm and inviting atmosphere that is synonymous with the Chawke name. We have installed a beautiful Beer Garden to the rear of Searson's complete with high definition screens for all your sporting pleasure. Heated and covered for those chilly days and nights but it can also be wonderfully open for those balmy summer occasions when the sun graces us with its presence! Our brand new 'state of the art' kitchen serves delicious food all day and our bars are stocked with the finest of Beers, Wines, Spirits & Liqueurs. We can cater for family occasions, after work parties and any other celebration you might have. Our Sunday Jazz sessions are an absolute must and we regularly have other live music playing at weekends and bank holiday Sundays, we also have a fantastic cocktail menu which changes regularly ...Come in and find your favourite!

details.locationDescription: • The Copper Alley Bistro at the Harding Hotel is situated in the heart of Dublin’s Cultural District, on the edge of Temple Bar and right beside one of Dublin’s most famous landmarks Christ Church Cathedral.• Copper Alley itself is a famous site which dates back to the 13th Century and follows the route of an earlier Viking street. During the 15th Century it was known as Parson’s Lane.• By the 17th Century it had become known as Copper Ally, taking its name from the money which was minted there. It was famous for it’s Taverns and Eating Houses and in 1742 the first performance of Handel’s Messiah was performed in a music hall nearby.• Copper Alley was also home to a famous Brothel run by a woman known as Darkey Kelly. • Copper Alley Bistro provides top value cuisine in a very relaxing, informal atmosphere. Out friendly & efficient staff will be delighted to attend to you on your visit.• Our renowned selection of Steaks, Seafood, Chicken and Vegetarian dishes are delicious and appealing to all. Restaurant sits approx 50 – 60 people Looking over the Christchurch Cathedral Opening Hours: Breakfast: 7.30am – 11.45am Monday – Sunday Lunch served from 12 noon – 4pm Evening Meals from 4pm – 10.00pm Early Bird Menu served from 4pm – 7pm.

details.locationDescription: The Bleeding Horse is a historically significant public house located in Upper Camden Street, Dublin, Ireland. It dates at least back to the 17th century, and was located on St. Kevin’s Port (now Camden St.) at the junction of two important highways leading out of the city.On one side was Charlotte St., leading to Ranelagh and Donnybrook; on the other side was Old Camden St., which joined Richmond St. and led to Rathmines and Cullenswood. Both of these old streets disappeared during the renovations in the 1990s. The present building dates from 1871; the interior was renovated in 1992.There are (at least) two explanations for the name. One is that when a horse got the “staggers” it was bled by a farrier at the inn. Another is that the name of the pub comes from an incident during the Battle of Rathmines in 1649, when a wounded horse fled from the battle.

details.locationDescription: An Irish pub is a warm, welcoming place where people socialize, relax, tell stories, and exchange gossip and rumors over a pint. Dublin’s Irish Pub will bring a bit of Ireland to Oshkosh, WI with an authentic, warm and welcoming teach tabhairne (“tavern-house”). It all began with a desire to bring something great to Oshkosh and the knowledge that there is nothing to equal the ambiance of an Irish pub, nothing to match its casual and attractive sociability. The Irish have always known that, now you can experience it. David Toman and Todd Ceman, the owners of Dublin’s, are committed to keep the Irish experience genuine. Drinks that provide the true flavor of Ireland are essential, such as Guinness, Harp, Jameson, Bushmills and Bailey’s Irish Cream. Distinctive Irish recipes and food are another important part of Irish pub life, attracting custom and adding ambiance. With 28 selections of craft beer on tap, you can’t find a better place in Wisconsin for an ice cold beer.

details.locationDescription: Book Your Special Event at Trinity Bar Venue Our dedicated function spaces can cater for any group, from as few as 10 to as many as 200 people. For no charge, you can reserve a private area, featuring your own bar, waitress service, and the choice to avail of either our full menu service, or finger-food platters. If you book for a group of fifteen and up to twenty people, we’ll even throw in those finger-food platters at no extra cost! Trinity Bar Venue will cater for any type of event: from birthday celebrations, Stag and Hen parties, or after-work drinks and leaving dos; to product launches, sporting and charity events, funeral afters, or even small weddings, our dedicated Events Team will be on hand at all times to make sure your party goes your way! Trinity Bar Venue Dublin´s Premier Sports Bar While we aim to offer variety at Trinity, there is one thing that always remains constant. That is the quality time you will get to spend here. Our quality goes beyond the taste and technology, a fact apparent from the crowds that gather here. From our extremely fun and friendly staff to the crazy crowd of fanatics who share your passion for rugby and sports, we have the best of lot here at Trinity Sports Bar. While most of them are young and energetic, you will also find plenty of old sports sharing their knowledge and stories to top off the fun. So, we have the venue, the menu, and an exciting crowd of people cheering for your favourite team. Plus, the biggest screen in Dublin that is all prepared to give you a crystal clear view of the most adrenaline filled experience this year. We are just in heart of Temple Bar and we will be showing all the matches. Make sure you have the schedule memorized so you don’t miss even the tiniest bit of action. If you like sports you have to come to Trinity Bar Venue Dublin´s Premier Sports Bar.

details.locationDescription: One of Dublin’s best kept secrets, Platform 61 offers imaginative food, elegant wines and extraordinary cocktails in the intimate surroundings of an underground hideaway on South William Street. Platform 61’s stunning setting takes its inspiration from a secret subway platform under the Waldorf Astoria in New York. The platform with its specially built golden elevator allowed VIPs such as President F.D. Roosevelt to access the hotel in private, and also played host to Andy Warhol’s infamous ‘Underground Parties’ Today, the platform known as Track 61 has become the holy grail for New York’s urban explorers seeking to uncover its legend, lore and legacy. In turn, Platform 61 has become the go-to venue for Dublin’s social urbanites seeking only the best in dining experiences. Come experience Platform 61 for yourself. Platform 61 – #BetterBeingUnderground

details.locationDescription: Step out of the bustling cobblestone streets of Temple Bar and down the stairs to Tomahawk Steakhouse where beautiful windows allow in light from street level. We have spent months researching where to source the best steaks from around the world and the results of that exploration is there is no better beef than Irish and we are proud to say that we serve only the market-best at Tomahawk. Tomahawk has 80 delightful seats for you and your party to choose from. snippet.text: I moved to Dublin last September and the first pub I stumbled across the
details.locationDescription: The Oval Bar is an authentic Irish Pub situated idyllically in the heart of Dublin City on Middle Abbey Street. Housed within a beautiful Victorian building with most of its period features still intact, The Oval is the perfect place to escape from the hectic hustle and bustle of the city outside and provides a haven of welcome and warmth for local office workers on lunch, busy shoppers looking to recharge their batteries, visiting tourists looking for the 'Craic' and music, cinema and theatre goers looking for a bite to eat and a drink before or after their show. Once our patrons step inside our doors they experience the relaxed and convivial nature of our charming pub, our Staff are welcoming and friendly and will ensure that everyone's stay is a pleasant one. With over 3 floors of seating and a large function area with its own private bar facilities available to rent we can accommodate any size group. We also have an outdoor seating area for those lazy Dublin summer evenings. Our kitchen serves a full menu daily with Traditional Irish Stew being one of our specialities! The Oval has long been renowned as an exceptional place to watch 'the match', we show all the major sporting events on our wide screen LCD TVs and has also a great atmosphere for pre or post match celebrations for patrons going to and from Croke Park. The Oval - home of the best Pint of Guinness in Dublin!

snippet.text: experience for delicious and unique drinks while on our honeymoon in Dublin
details.locationDescription: During Prohibition, there were two types of venues where you could get a drink: a ‘blind pig’ or ‘blind tiger’ was a venue that catered more to the lower class with dancing and live music, serving beer and poorly-made moonshine -- sometimes even produced on the premises itself. The second type of venue was a speakeasy which was a luxurious hidden venue aimed at the upper class, where the finest alcohol was acquired and talented bartenders were brought in to mix delicious cocktails for famous movie stars and politicians of the day. The Little Pig, hidden away in the heart of Dublin city, is a nod to these beautiful rooms of years past with plush décor, fine wines and the highest quality spirits. The sister bar to The Blind Pig, is a truly sophisticated and opulent 1920s speakeasy.

details.locationDescription: Restaurant 104 is an award winning restaurant in the heart of Drumcondra. A local favourite, we are open 7 days a week, from 9am to 10pm. details.locationDescription: Started in 2002, Jaipur Dalkey has always aimed to create fresh & seasonal dishes that are an interpretation of customary Indian sensibilities through our use of international techniques & inspirations. With the re-opening of Jaipur Dalkey in 2020, owner Asheesh Dewan has decided to combine his two great loves - Food & Art. With a whole new look for the interiors, the walls host some of his favourite artwork by artists from all over the world. A truer Indian experience you won’t find, with manager Prashant(aka Shan) and team always on-hand to welcome you to this elegantly decorated restaurant where Indian style is reshaped into a modern contemporary design. This elegance is replicated on the plate where local ingredients are transformed into classic Indian dishes. details.locationDescription: There’s not much more you could need from a cocktail bar, stylish, sophisticated, cool, unique with a great atmosphere and in the heart of Dublin cities nightspots & shopping district. We have an extensive menu offering homemade classic and contemporary dishes served by a team of top of the industry waiters, bartenders and chefs. Zozimus is on the ground floor of Centenary House, Anne’s Lane in Dublin, where our famous umbrellas structure perfectly captures the vibrant and artistic spirit of the area. Flying the flag for our colourful personality and charm, our umbrellas have become somewhat of our calling card, giving insight into the vibrant cocktails and characters which await inside. Pronounced Zoz-e-mus, our bar got its name from Irish street rhymer Michael J Moran (1794 – 1846) who was more fondly known as Zozimus. Blinded by illness at just two weeks old, Zozimus made his living reciting poems in his own lively style, many of which he had composed himself.

snippet.text: Dall italia is the most incredible pasta in Dublin.
details.locationDescription: Authentic Italian homemade fresh pasta and sauces. 100% Natural , No conservants or preservatives! Pasta Bar Dall'Italia (from Italy) is a small, lively, unique fast food establishment focused on offering high quality, nutritious fresh Italian pasta dishes and centered around display cooking, so the customers can engage with our highly qualified chef in the meal preparation process. Dall'Italia Pastabar provides quick and efficient service of our freshly prepared pasta dishes, to be served in suitable take-away packaging for the customers upmost convience. Although fast food is not a new concept, our model is: to produce freshly made, traditional Italian pasta and sauces, served quickly, at a fraction of the price of sit down resataurant, whilst retaining the highest quality. Furthermore, our Pastabar reinvents the pasta experience for take-out customers with limited budgets, by selling high quality products at affordable prices, giving the customers opportunity to choose as many ingredients to go into their creation and taste. Our fresh sauces will be cooked in store using fresh ingredients. Our pasta bar will promote healthy traditional Italian pasta dishes accompanied by side salads and homemade desserts: Tiramisu and cannoli Siciliani. We want our customers to have the TOTAL experience when visiting our outlet, and through our website learn about this new fascinating pasta bar.

details.locationDescription: The Dropping Well is a landmark pub located in the Suburb of Milltown in South Dublin, just down the road from The Nine Arches with panoramic views of the beautiful Dodder River. A fine traditional bar which has been extensively renovated over the years to provide our patrons with a superior atmosphere and exceptional facilities. The Dropping Well can cater for all of our patrons needs whether that be a family function in our rustic 'Dodder' function room, a large corporate event in our well appointed 'Bank' function room, a sumptuous meal in our Classons Restaurant, an outdoor BBQ or a simple quiet pint in one of the bars or out on the sun terrace. We show all the major sports events on our state of the art 3D and LCD TV screens, host many live bands and DJs and have a wealth of golf outings, wine tastings and other promotional nights for our customers enjoyment. Our Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner and Function Menus are constantly being updated to provide a superior seasonal dining experience and we also have a very large and varied wine list and rare liquor stock. The Dropping Well is easily accessible as the Milltown Luas Station is very close by and we have a large customer car park. Our Management, Bar, Floor & Kitchen Staff work as a close knit team to ensure that patrons of The Dropping Well have the best possible experience during their time with us no matter how short their stay!

details.locationDescription: Rosie's Cafe is run by a small team of food lovers determined to bring you the freshest and most wholesome choice of salads, breakfasts, lunches and sweet treats. All our food is prepared daily on premises which guarantees the highest quality meal for you to enjoy. We offer a wide range of gourmet salads, wraps, paninis and sandwiches all freshly prepared to your liking. Hot lunches such a lasagne, pies,burritos, quiche and soup are served daily along with our breakfast and vegan menu. We also serve fresh juices, seasonal smoothies, a wide selection of herbal teas and of course our gourmet coffee courtesy of McCabe's hand roasted coffee company in County Wicklow. And not forgetting a decadent choice of desserts is always available including cakes, tarts and pastries all lovingly prepared in our own kitchen. At Rosie's Cafe we are open 5 days a week and look forward to your visit.

snippet.text: A must try if getting lunch in Dublin, GA.
details.locationDescription: Brian's Giant Subs is a family-owned and operated, Jersey-style sandwich business located in Dublin, GA. The business was founded and opened as a start-up on April 25, 1989. Brian’s operated under a small franchise for a couple of years, before branching off and building its own successful local brand more commonly known as, Brian's Giant Subs. Brian's specializes in made-to-order cold and hot subs with fresh-sliced meats and cheeses per order, daily fresh-baked bread, and fresh condiments. While serving quality food is a must, the customer experience is a large part of what makes Brian's such a successful business. With decades of experience in the sandwich business dating back to 1989, Brian's values its customers as family and friends. Brian's Subs offers old-fashioned service and customer satisfaction that in today’s society seems so hard to find. Come give us a try! We are a CASH only business, so no debit or credit.

details.locationDescription:
Dublin 2

Opening Hours:
12.00 til Late (Mon - Sat)
Food: 12-9.30pm

This year Mc Grattans celebrates it's 21st anniversary. It was originally known as a one of Dublin's most famous Restaurant's but in recent times it's become one of the cities best loved pub grub venues. Not only that there's the only beer-garden in the Baggot Street area, comfortable surroundings, a laid-back atmosphere and even a couple of pool tables.

The list of celeb's that have passed through Mc Grattans includes U2, Uma Thurmann, Oliver Reed, Pavarotti, in fact too many to mention. But it's not the kind of place to feel star-struck. It's one of the friendliest bars around with great areas for private parties and gatherings. 

Mc Grattans not only does great value food and drink all week but at the weekends turns into a late night destination for some of the cities hippest party goers. A real gem that needs to be explored.

McGrattans Cafe Bar
76 Fitzwilliam Lane
(Just off Baggot St)
Dublin 2
Ireland
Bookings: + 353 1 6618808

details.locationDescription: The savoury crêpes are made from buckwheat flour (a naturally gluten free product) while the sweet crêpes are made from wheat flour. For authenticity our crêpes are made from flour produced in a Brittany mill, and imported directly. When crêpes were first made in the 15th century in Brittany they were considered peasant food. Over time simple fillings were added and many remain popular today. At Le Petit Breton we’ve kept some of these old favourites such as La Complète (egg, ham and cheese) but have added more contemporary options showcasing the best of Irish produce (see our full menu here). We sincerely hope you enjoy every bite.

details.locationDescription: Citron Restaurant in one of Dublin’s hippest, Conran-designed hotels is found at the very heart of town just opposite St Stephen’s Green. The ambience is Euro-bistro and the modern Mediterranean cuisine is perfectly attuned to how we eat now.
